
Installing nps-ssh-askpass:

The easiest way to install is to run:  sudo ./install

Otherwise, the program (nps-ssh-askpass) should be placed in a directory
that is on your execution path.  /usr/bin or ~/bin are usually good
choices.  Copy the libraries in lib/ to a directory on your
LD_LIBRARY_PATH.


Running nps-ssh-askpass:

If you find bugs, please check the web page to see if they have already
been reported.

On OS X, this program requires XQuartz, the X11 server.  Before running
this program, you must first start XQuartz.


Notes on nps-ssh-askpass:

nps-ssh-askpass does exactly the same job as x11-ssh-askpass, but it's not
as hard to compile on Mac OS X, because it doesn't require xmkmf.


The main Web page for nps-ssh-askpass is

    http://sourceforge.net/p/nps-ssh-askpass/

